-

A mandala represents a spiritual journey, starting from the outside to the inner core. A mandala represents transformation, change, and cycles. I tattooed mandalas on my arm to remind me of this: your life is ever-changing— fitness included! Just like on my own journey, transformation started on the outside with my fitness, but ripped to my inner core. It strengthened confidence, spirituality, self love and brought me so much peace. Fitness can be represented as the outer-part of the mandala, but everything that comes along with that change is the change through & deep to the core, like the mandala. Every time you use these resistance bands, I want you to actively remember the transformation you’re activity under-doing. I want you to remember that I am right there with you, holding your hand through your transformation🦋
⠀ 
✨GIVEAWAY✨I’m giving away ALL 6 BANDS to 1 lucky winners! You’ll have the complete collection🤫 All you have to do:
1️⃣Like this post

3️⃣Tag 3 friends
4️⃣Winner randomly chosen at the end of the weekend🌸

node.text:
COOK WITH ME!👩🏽‍🍳 Walk-through🍝🥒
⠀ 
This specific recipe serves 3! Feel free to adjust as needed for your needs🥰
⠀ 
INGREDIENTS⬇️
2 cloves garlic
1/2 onion or 1/2 c chopped onion
12 oz raw lean beef (using 93/7 here)
1/2 Tbsp olive oil
1/2 c chopped mushrooms 
1 tsp garlic powder
1 tsp onion powder
1 tsp dried basil
1 tsp dried oregano
1 tsp salt
1/2 tsp red pepper flakes
15 oz spiraled or peeled zucchini (about 5 oz per serving)
⠀ 
INSTRUCTIONS⬇️
1️⃣Peel or spiralize noodles. I recommend letting them sit in paper towels overnight so it absorbs moisture! This will keep your sauce from becoming watery
2️⃣Cut 2 cloves of garlic & chop 1/2 c worth of onions
3️⃣Brown 12 oz beef then remove from the pan
4️⃣Add 1/2 Tbsp olive oil to your hot pan & add the onion. Let the onions brown & soften, about 5 minutes
5️⃣Add garlic & stir until fragrant 
6️⃣Add chopped mushrooms & stir until soft, about 2 minutes
7️⃣Add back in your browed beef & 1 c pureed tomatoes 
8️⃣Add your spices & stir 
9️⃣Let the sauce summer until slightly thickened, about 2-3 minutes. It’s good to go when it begins sticking to the bottom of the pan!
1️⃣0️⃣Mix in your raw zucchini noodles & toss until slightly cooked
1️⃣1️⃣Serve! Top with some grated parm (DUH!)
⠀ 
CALS/MACROS PER SERVING⬇️
360 CALS, 36 g carbs, 13 g fat, 32 g protein
⠀ 
Let me know if you liked this walk-through style of cooking video!👩🏽‍🍳💕

GIRL’S NIGHT OUT WRAP 2:00 (new)

node.text:
The most effective, yet least-spoken-about piece of the Covid-19 puzzle: course, please respect guidelines/protocols of your current state or country of residence, but follow these essential tips!!🙌🏽
⠀ 
Gut health
70-80% of your gut makes up your immune system!
Tips: hydration, supplement opti-greens (probiotics, digestive enzymes, superfoods) to fill the gaps & provide additional support (link in bio)
⠀ 
Nourish your body
Loads of fruits + vegetables full of Vitamin C + anti-oxidants! Garlic is also an immunity superfood (caution: high FODMAP for those w/ gut concerns)
Add in the opti-reds for additional anti-oxidant support, anti-aging, and immunity (link in bio)
⠀ 
Exercise + movement!
Stay active throughout the day, create an exercise schedule that is maintainable for you, keep your heart healthy
⠀ 
Sleep
Practice a routine at nighttime to get you ready for a deep rest. Shut-off decides, dark + cold room, wind-down... quality sleep is key to not only immunity but fat loss, muscle growth, recovery and more
⠀ 
Vitamin-D
42% of the U.S. is deficient! Main source is sunlight but as many are deficient, I recommend supplementing with the liposomal Vitamin D for your overall health, energy, immunity and bones
⠀ 
Healthy Fats
Help reduce inflammation! When you’re sick, your body will become inflamed to fight off X. If it is already in a state of chronic inflammation, it will prolong recovery and hinder optimal immune system - Omega-3’s are great to supplement here as most do not get in the daily recommendation
⠀ 
Weight Management
Maintain a healthy BF%, lean body mass, and strive for the healthiest version of you! Focus on overall health & immunity and weight or aesthetics will fall shortly after!
⠀ 
YOU have control of your health! Let’s keep ourselves and those around us happy & healthy👊🏽
⠀ 
Link in my bio to the supplements I mentioned with free shipping today!! 💸

node.text:
FRENCH TOAST PANCAKES!🥞🍞Say whaaaaat🙀
⠀ 
Coping another Broncos loss with some bomb ass PANCAKES!🥞
⠀ 
I can personally eat pancakes ANY time of day, so be sure to try these out!😊 Great for pre/post workout since it’s very high in protein and low in fat!
⠀ 
EASIEST recipe ever👏🏼😩
Blend 4 slices of bread with 184 g egg whites, cinnamon, stevia, vanilla, and salt to taste
Cook on a stove top on medium heat with non-stick spray
Add desired toppings!
Top with your favorite (I used walden farms)
Perfect, fluffy pancakes done in < 5 minutes!!
⠀ 
HIGH in protein, LOW in fat🙏🏽
#FOOTBALLSUNDAYSERIES BABY!🏈 ⠀ 
Tag a friend to make some pancakes with down below😏👇🏽

node.text:
Skinny Piña Colada, anyone?🍹🍍 Use your leftover pineapple from my fried rice recipe to make these😋 (on my reels!)
⠀ 
BLEND⬇️
1.5 c fresh pineapple 🍍
120 mL unsweetened coconut milk 🥥
200 mL Malibu (or rum of choice) 🌴
4 c ice 🧊 
💭adjust Malibu amount to your preference
⠀ 
Traditional piña colada: 472-650 calories😅
Mine: 235 cals each & low in fat💃🏽🏝🍍
⠀ 
Sipping on this’ll have ya feeling like you’re sitting on a beach 🏖😎 ENJOY!
#cocktail #recipe #pinacolada #reels

node.text:
My best friend! I love you!!!♥️
⠀ 
I honestly think the last time we worked out was when we took this picture a couple weeks ago😅 We’ve been painting & renovating all of the floors in our house..things have been CRAZY (shared a before/after in my story!) You know EXACTLY what I mean if you’ve gone through any sort of remodel🙃 Hobby Lobby & Home Goods have been getting more attention than the gym… which is fine by me😉 but in all seriousness, life gets crazy sometimes. Or, you need to mentally take a few steps back from things. WHATEVER it is…you have to give yourself grace during times where the gym isn’t on the top of your priority list. Your muscles won’t disappear and your progress won’t make a 180– I promise. Don’t dig yourself a hole of guilt & fear that all of your progress is “ruined.” Just try to stay active, stay hydrated, be *mindful* with your nutrition & protein intake, then get back into it when you can🥰 That’s what makes it a lifestyle; NO “all or nothing” mentality😎
⠀ 
Wishing you an amazing weekend 😋 xo

node.text:
Crunch wraps are always the GOAT for late night muchies!😩 Here’s a low calorie version you can quickly throw together whenever you’re craving one🤩
⠀ 
MINE ➡️246 CALORIES (32 C / 8 F / 27 P 🤯
Taco Bell’s➡️530 CALORIES (71 C / 21 F / 16 P)
⠀ 
1️⃣Cut your corn tortilla as appropriate to the size of your low carb flour tortilla. Then, air fry at 400 degrees for about 5 minutes flipping half way through
⠀ 
2️⃣Once cooled, assemble! On your low carb tortilla, add your seasoned low fat ground beef (2 oz), fat free cheese (1/2 serving), corn chip, FF sour cream or NF Greek yogurt (1-2 Tbsp), lettuce & tomato
⠀ 
3️⃣Fold in the sides. Place face down on the air fryer & spray the top with non-stick spray. Cook at 400 for about 5 minutes or until golden brown!
⠀ 
#healthyrecipes #lowcarb #lowcalorie #crunchwrap

It’s BACK DAYYYYY, hunnnniiiii🤩 Building those curves with a strong back⏳👌🏽
⠀ 
Save this back day to crush later! Your lats will be FEEEELINGGG it tomorrow🥵😉
⠀ 
1️⃣Alternating bicep curls 4 x 8, 10, 12, 20
💭Notice how I’m turning the weight as I’m bringing it up
⠀ 
2️⃣Single arm machine row 2 x 12, 2 x 8
💭Keep tension on your lat here: you want it tight the entire time
⠀ 
3️⃣DB Hammer curls 3 x 15-20
⠀ 
4️⃣DB bent over row 4 x 10-12
⠀ 
5️⃣Single arm machine low row 4 x 8, 10, 12, 15
⠀ 
🌟Be sure to adjust the weight you’re using to the reps
🌟If your gym doesn’t have the row machines, you can sub with cables
⠀ 
Song: Wherever I may roam, J Balvin x Metallica
Leggings are @nvgtn & bra is @paragonfitwear (links are in my bio!🌺🤩)
#backworkout #backday #biceps #gym

How cute are these pineapple chicken “fried rice” bowls?🍍😍 These are a MUST try! 🤤
⠀ 
High in protein & fiber, lower carb, fresh, quick & delicious🤗
⠀ 
Ingredients
🍍1 bag frozen or fresh cauliflower rice (340 g)
🍍1/2 bag mixed frozen or fresh veggies (170 g)
🍍1/2 Tbsp sesame oil
🍍8 oz cooked chicken breast
🍍4 Tbsp egg beaters (or egg whites)
🍍1/4 c tamari (GF soy sauce), or soy sauce or coconut aminos (for a soy & GF option)
🍍1 pineapple
⠀ 
1️⃣Heat a large pan & lightly coat with sesame oil
2️⃣Add 1 frozen bag of cauliflower fried rice & 1/2 bag mixed veggies. Keep stirring until it begins to warm
3️⃣Add cooked chicken breast
4️⃣Add about tamari/soy sauce/coconut aminos to the pan & stir
5️⃣Add in about cubed pineapple & stir until combined 
6️⃣Serve in your pineapple boat & garnish with green onion. Be sure to save the leftover pineapple for another recipe👌🏽😉
⠀ 
Serves 2🥰 MACROS⬇️
370 calories / 45 G protein / 30 G carbs / 8 G fat 😎

Full workout is below🤟🏽 COMPLETE shoulder annihilation😮‍💨 in the best way possible😜
⠀ 
Want to see progress with your delts?😍 Volume, volume, volume & time under tension is KEY🔑
⠀ 
Try these holds & supersets for an insane workout 🔥
⠀ 
1️⃣lateral raise w/ 2-second hold
🌺4x12-15
⠀ 
2️⃣reverse shoulder press
🌺1x6, 1x10, 1x15, 1x25
⠀ 
SUPERSET
3️⃣alternating bicep curl w/iso hold (threw them in bc why not!)
🌺3x12 each side
4️⃣power rear delt raise (KEEP THIS CONTROLLED for the safety of your shoulder)
🌺3x12 each side
⠀ 
GIANT SET (all exercises back to back)
5️⃣alternating front raise
🌺4x12 each side
6️⃣cable lateral raise w/ hold
🌺4x12 each side
7️⃣machine rear delt fly
🌺4x15-20
⠀ 
8️⃣alternating Arnold press
🌺4x12
⠀ 
You’ll want to be sure to save this one😏🔥

13 NO B.S. Ways to #AddMassToThatAss 🤫🍑
⠀ 
LAST CHANCE to get my FREE Booty Ebook & Exercise Program (link in bio)⏰👆🏽
⠀ 
Feel like you’ve been running around in circles with your progress?😅BELIEVE ME, I’ve been there- that was me for years! These 13 tips, methods & protocols WILL FINALLY move your booty progress in the right direction!🙌🏽
⠀ 
1️⃣Cardio does NOT ”build/tone” your glutes. We LOVE cardio for heart health & as a tool to burn calories… but NOT to build muscle. Although you might feel “burning” from said cardio, that is not a significant stimulus to build muscle. What is? Lifting weights! Cut the kickbacks on the stair master & endless squat jumps & supersets! Don’t be afraid to pick up the weights.. your body & booty will thank you
⠀ 
2️⃣Poor exercise selection is hindering progress. We all see “sexy” exercises here on the gram. Truth is: just because someone’s butt looks good doing them doesn’t mean they’re actually effective. Dial in/LOAD exercises that DIRECTLY load the glutes (ex. squats/hip thrusts) vs. facing backwards on the abduction machine, ie. I also consider exercises that you cannot perform properly/ones that don’t “feel good” poor exercise selection! Don’t waste time and energy on, simply put, 🗑 “trendy” movements
⠀ 
3️⃣You’re not training hard enough. Do you know what it feels like to take a set to TRUE failure? Like, you physically CANNOT do another rep? THAT is what you want to bring sets to. I used to do WAY too many exercises during my workout thinking more was better…You don’t have to do as many sets/exercises if you just pushed your sets harder: more isn’t better. PUSH past the burn & discomfort. Your body is capable of much more than you think
⠀ 
Want insight on the other 1️⃣0️⃣? It’s FREE!😍 I got over HOW to train & why, nutrition & I’ve included a free exercise program in there for you😏💪🏽
⠀ 
How to get it?➡️Have made or make ANY 1st Phorm purchase through my personal link (in my bio) for the month of JULY. Enter my monthly giveaway & you get this free ebook in return! EVERYONE is a winner this month😩😍
⠀ 
Click the link in my bio & follow the instructions to get your FREE Ebook to #AddMassToThatAss 👌🏽🍑

node.text:
Target your QUADS with these exercises 🔑 Which one of these is your favorite?🔥
⠀ 
What do I mean by “keeping tension on your quads?” ➡️ DON’T fully “lock out!” I want you to think about coming 95% of the way up
⠀ 
✅Pressure in the HEELS
✅Push OUT against the working knee(s)
✅Try the narrow stances & elevated front foot!
⠀ 
Give these a try for the ULTIMATE quad burn😏🔥
#quads #legworkout #reels #workout

LEGGIESSS at the old stomping ground😈 Back home for a quick couple of days visiting fam & celebrating my moms birthday!☺️ Had to put the pizza…and bagels…and wine…and more pizza from yesterday to WORK (see my story)👌🏽🤪
⠀ 
Save this strong legs workout 🏋🏽‍♀️😤 & share with someone to crush it with👯‍♀️🍑
⠀ 
1️⃣Smith machine squat w/ pause (at the bottom) • 4x15
💭wanted to show you the front AND back here: watch how tight my core is the entire time, chest is up & glutes are fully engaged
⠀ 
2️⃣DB sumo squat • 4x10
💭push those knees OUT the entire time. Back flat, chest up!
⠀ 
3️⃣DB split squat • 4x12
💭slightly lean forward to shift focus on the glutes. Drop the weight straight down & keep pressure in the heels
⠀ 
4️⃣Glute focused leg press • 1x25, 1x15, 1x8, 1xfail (adjust weight each set)
💭don’t let your lower back lift at the bottom on the lowering phase. I slightly paused at the bottom to get a really good stretch in the glutes
⠀ 
4 exercises was all that was needed to feel 🥵🥵🥵👌🏽 Enjoy the SICK leg pump 😉
⠀ 
Shorts @nvgtn 
#legworkout #quads #legday #glutes

node.text:
FRENCH TOAST STICKS w/ a blueberry maple🍁🫐 dipping sauce that is TO DIE FOR🥵 
⠀ 
✅HIGH Protein
✅LOW cal
✅FIBER
✅Sweet, fun & delicious 😋
⠀ 
Growing up, French toast sticks were my FAVORITE breakfast (of course, paired with an entire bottle of maple syrup🤣)
⠀ 
Here’s my delicious, protein-packed version⬇️😍
⠀ 
Ingredients✅
6-7 slices low cal bread (using Sara Lee 45 cal)
1 egg
5 egg whites (or ~ 184 g)
Dash of vanilla
2 Tbsp almond milk (unsweetened)
1/2 Tbsp cinnamon
Sweetener of choice
⠀ 
Instructions⬇️
💭Cut your bread into 1/3 slices
💭Beat all of your other ingredients
💭Batter your bread & assemble in the air fryer with non-stick spray
💭Air fry for a total of 6 minutes at 370 degrees, flipping 1/2 way through
⠀ 
Optional dipping sauce🙌🏽🫐🍁
Mix 1 c frozen blueberries & 1/4 c sugar free maple syrup. Microwave for 1 min & stir!😍
⠀ 
⠀ 
⠀ 
#macrofriendly #reels #recipe #highprotein #mealideas #breakfast #frenchtoast #yummy #food #nutrition #diet #fit

node.text:
Feel free to pick & choose any of these swaps next time you’re out to eat!🥰
⠀ 
I used to FEAR going out to eat thinking it would derail me from my fitness goals😅…but remember, YOU are in control!
⠀ 
These tips will help you shave down HUNDREDS of calories from the meal & support your fat loss goal! Now, do you “have to” make ANY of these swaps? Heck no! It’s all about calories in/out & consuming what makes you feel best. Eat in accordance to your goals.
⠀ 
Here, I chose to have a lower-carb meal & balanced it with a couple skinny margs! If I didn’t have the margs, I definitely would of enjoyed normal tortillas or rice! Like I said, all about what makes YOU feel best: find that balance for you.
⠀ 
Mexican food is ALWAYS our go-to😋 Try these simple tips next time you’re out to eat!
